Visual Studio Code Setup for AI Projects

Prerequisites:

Visual Studio Code (VSCode) installed
Python 3.6 or later
Git
Step 1: Install Python Extension

Open VSCode and go to the Extensions tab.
Search for "Python" and install the official Python extension.
Step 2: Install Jupyter Extension

Search for "Jupyter" in the Extensions tab.
Install the "Jupyter" extension.
Step 3: Create a Virtual Environment

Open a terminal in VSCode (Ctrl + `).
Create a new virtual environment:
python3 -m venv venv
Activate the virtual environment:
source venv/bin/activate
Step 4: Install Required Packages

Install the necessary packages for your AI project. For example, for TensorFlow:
pip install tensorflow
Step 5: Create a Jupyter Notebook

In VSCode, go to File > New > Jupyter Notebook.
Save the notebook in your project directory.
Step 6: Run the Notebook

Click the "Run" button in the notebook toolbar.
Your code will execute in the Jupyter kernel.
Additional Tips:

Use the "Python Interactive" window in VSCode to test code snippets.
Install the "Code Spell Checker" extension for improved code readability.
Use the "GitLens" extension for version control integration.
Troubleshooting:

If you encounter errors, check the Python and Jupyter extension settings.
Ensure that your virtual environment is activated.
Restart VSCode if you experience any issues.
